---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Ed Barlow — Ed Barlow">
  <section class="home-hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">

      <div class="hero-text">
        <h1 class="home-name">Ed Barlow</h1>
        <div class="home-body">
<h2>Current Project:  The GAME Framework for Agentic Development</h2>
<p>I have combined my <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Process-Based-Database-Administration-Management-ebook/dp/B073RRQBZC">Process Based Methodology</a> and scale-proven <a href="https://webcloudstudio.github.io/webcloudstudio/project-docs/Specifications/Features.html">Technology Rules</a> into an agentic developer Framework.</p>
<p>The concept is exciting.  Contact me if you want to collaborate.</p>
<p><strong>Summary</strong>: LLMs enable developers to create quickly. The creations differ and do not work together.  The GAME framework provides a best practice stack and a mechanism to "conform" projects such that they work together, work in the same way, and be managed from a single pane of glass.  GAME provides full observability inside a professional devops workflow.</p>
<p>Key Concept: Annotations and Scripts expose project capabilities in a uniform way with no code impact.</p>
<p>Key Concept: Agents enforce best practices, branding, and security - easily customized defaults provided (its text)</p>
<p>Key Concept: A Capability Catalog disovers project capabilities and advertises these as a complete tools catalog (MCP for python) </p>
<p>Key Concept: Capabilities include services, data, and servers.  You share your technologies securely and use your capabilities in your Agentic Development.</p>
<p>Key Concept: Conformed code is enables an enterprise command center with enterprise features like Logging, Monitoring &amp; Alerting, Scheduling, Pipelines...</p>
<h3>The GAME Framework contains</h3>
<ul>
<li>A <strong>Command Center</strong> provides namespaced views into your projects.</li>
<li>A <strong>Capability Catalog</strong> broadcasts/shares your tooling in a "MCP for python" manner (transport agnostic: REST, CLI, Async, MCP)</li>
<li>A <strong>Prototyper</strong> enables context aware reproducible builds from base specifications for home developers</li>
<li><strong>Simple Workflows</strong> enable control of your projects and change management</li>
</ul>
<h3>OUT OF THE BOX Enterprise Operations</h3>
<p>Monitoring, Documentation, Scheduled tasks, Security, Data Flows, and Sharing of your "STUFF".</p>
<h3>Who I am</h3>
<p><strong>Hands On Backend Technology Leader</strong> at hedge funds, investment banks, insurance companies, and startups </p>
<p><strong>Author</strong>, <strong>Speaker</strong>, <strong>Free Software Developer</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-photo">
        <img src="/images/portrait.jpg" alt="Ed Barlow" class="portrait" />
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .home-hero { padding: 3rem 0 4rem; }

    .hero-inner {
      max-width: 1280px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 0 1.5rem;
      display: flex;
      gap: 4rem;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .hero-text { flex: 1; min-width: 0; }

    .home-name {
      font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem);
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      margin: 0 0 2rem;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .hero-photo {
      flex: 0 0 360px;
      width: 360px;
      padding-top: 0.5rem;
    }

    .portrait {
      width: 100%;
      aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
      object-fit: cover;
      border-radius: 12px;
      border: 1px solid #252540;
      box-shadow: 0 8px 48px rgba(79, 156, 249, 0.08);
      display: block;
    }

    @media (max-width: 960px) {
      .hero-inner { flex-direction: column-reverse; gap: 2rem; }
      .hero-photo { flex: none; width: 100%; max-width: 480px; }
    }

    .home-body p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.75;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
    }

    .home-body h2 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    }

    .home-body h3 {
      font-size: 1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 1.75rem 0 0.6rem;
    }

    .home-body ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .home-body li {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--muted);
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
      position: relative;
    }

    .home-body li::before {
      content: '—';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      color: var(--accent);
    }

    .home-body strong { color: var(--text); font-weight: 600; }

    .home-body a { color: var(--accent); }
    .home-body a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .home-body em {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-style: italic;
      font-size: 0.92rem;
    }
  </style>
</Layout>
